[
    {
        "content": "<p>It's common in C to do something like this</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"C\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">struct</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">spdm_header</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">u8</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">version</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">u8</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">code</span><span class=\"p\">;</span><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"cm\">/* RequestResponseCode */</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">u8</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">param1</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">u8</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">param2</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">__packed</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"kt\">ssize_t</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">my_function</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"kt\">void</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"n\">req</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">size_t</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">req_sz</span><span class=\"p\">,)</span>\n<span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">struct</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">spdm_header</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"n\">request</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">req</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"p\">...</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>What's the preferred way to do something similar in Rust?</p>\n<p>I was thinking of a <code>From</code> implementation and a <code>from_raw_parts()</code>/<code>from_raw_parts_mut()</code>, something like this (untested).</p>\n<p>The issue is that <code>From</code> can't fail, so I'm not sure what to do if the From fails if an illegal value is supplied.</p>\n<p>Is there a better way I'm not thinking of?</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"cp\">#[repr(C, packed)]</span>\n<span class=\"k\">struct</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">SpdmHeader</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">version</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">u8</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">code</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">u8</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"cm\">/* RequestResponseCode */</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">param1</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">u8</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">param2</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">u8</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">From</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"kt\">u8</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">SpdmHeader</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">from</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">array</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"kt\">u8</span><span class=\"p\">])</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">SpdmHeader</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"c1\">// What happens on a failure? There is no result</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"fm\">todo!</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">ssize_t</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">my_function</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">void</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"n\">req</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">size_t</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">req_sz</span><span class=\"p\">,)</span>\n<span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">msg_buf</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">from_raw_parts_mut</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">req</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">req_sz</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">};</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">SpdmHeader</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">from</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">msg_buf</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"o\">..</span><span class=\"p\">.</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 475758878,
        "sender_full_name": "Alistair",
        "timestamp": 1728455134
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It really depends on what kind of void pointer this is. Is a bunch of bytes you just got from userspace?</p>",
        "id": 475768663,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1728457351
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>There is also the untrusted work from benno which might be a good thing to use here as well</p>",
        "id": 475801030,
        "sender_full_name": "Fiona Behrens",
        "timestamp": 1728464557
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It's a bunch of bytes from a device. So not userspace, but the data is untrusted. Although we can be confident of the number of bytes at least</p>",
        "id": 475805175,
        "sender_full_name": "Alistair",
        "timestamp": 1728465699
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Do you have a link to that?</p>",
        "id": 475805221,
        "sender_full_name": "Alistair",
        "timestamp": 1728465716
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The untrusted patch is <a href=\"https://lore.kernel.org/rust-for-linux/20240925205244.873020-1-benno.lossin@proton.me/#r\">here</a>. But that's not landed at all yet, so you probably want to use what exists today.</p>",
        "id": 475805742,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1728465884
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>This is all being built on not yet upstream SPDM patches, so I'm happy to pull in some more out of tree patches if it's the right approach long term</p>",
        "id": 475805938,
        "sender_full_name": "Alistair",
        "timestamp": 1728465940
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Please see here in Binder:<br>\n<a href=\"https://android.googlesource.com/kernel/common/+/refs/heads/android-mainline-rust/drivers/android/binder/defs.rs#128\">https://android.googlesource.com/kernel/common/+/refs/heads/android-mainline-rust/drivers/android/binder/defs.rs#128</a><br>\n<a href=\"https://android.googlesource.com/kernel/common/+/refs/heads/android-mainline-rust/drivers/android/binder/process.rs#1108\">https://android.googlesource.com/kernel/common/+/refs/heads/android-mainline-rust/drivers/android/binder/process.rs#1108</a></p>",
        "id": 475806214,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1728466008
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Or ashmem:<br>\n<a href=\"https://android-review.git.corp.google.com/c/kernel/common/+/3267327/8/drivers/staging/android/ashmem_rust.rs\">https://android-review.git.corp.google.com/c/kernel/common/+/3267327/8/drivers/staging/android/ashmem_rust.rs</a> (look at the top of <code>pin_unpin</code>)</p>",
        "id": 475806442,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1728466067
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thanks, I'll dig into those tomorrow</p>",
        "id": 475806655,
        "sender_full_name": "Alistair",
        "timestamp": 1728466120
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Though this is specific to reading from userspace. You'll probably need to do something similar to what's in the <code>kernel::uaccess</code> module (which the above examples use).</p>",
        "id": 475806820,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1728466168
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>we do have the <code>FromBytes</code> and <code>AsBytes</code> traits</p>",
        "id": 475830629,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1728472411
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>but they are missing the respective functions, though someone is working on that: <a href=\"https://github.com/Rust-for-Linux/linux/issues/1119\">https://github.com/Rust-for-Linux/linux/issues/1119</a></p>",
        "id": 475830835,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1728472455
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>For completeness there is also <a href=\"https://doc.rust-lang.org/stable/core/convert/trait.TryFrom.html\"><code>TryFrom</code></a> which is allowed to fail.</p>",
        "id": 476124920,
        "sender_full_name": "Andreas Hindborg",
        "timestamp": 1728564264
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Ah, I always forget about TryFrom. Thanks.</p>\n<p>I ended up going with the Unstrusted work from <a href=\"https://lore.kernel.org/rust-for-linux/20240925205244.873020-1-benno.lossin@proton.me\">https://lore.kernel.org/rust-for-linux/20240925205244.873020-1-benno.lossin@proton.me</a>, it's exactly what I was looking for</p>",
        "id": 476295526,
        "sender_full_name": "Alistair",
        "timestamp": 1728620560
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Another question. I feel like I have a good solution for fixed size structs, but now I'm a bit stuck with how to handle this for trailing array structs. Any ideas?</p>\n<p>Ideally I want to convert the bytes to a vector of <code>u16</code>s, but Vec doesn't work with a pointer cast</p>",
        "id": 476957694,
        "sender_full_name": "Alistair",
        "timestamp": 1728988441
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>That's a bit more tricky, but can be done. Could you share a struct so I can show an example?</p>",
        "id": 476958160,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1728988590
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>This is the C struct (not in mainline)</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"C\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">struct</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">spdm_get_version_rsp</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">u8</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">version</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">u8</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">code</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">u8</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">param1</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">u8</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">param2</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">u8</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">reserved</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">u8</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">version_number_entry_count</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">__le16</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">version_number_entries</span><span class=\"p\">[]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">__counted_by</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">version_number_entry_count</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">__packed</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 476958287,
        "sender_full_name": "Alistair",
        "timestamp": 1728988640
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>and ideally something like this</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"c1\">// Doesn't work, just an example</span>\n<span class=\"cp\">#[repr(C, packed)]</span>\n<span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"k\">crate</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">struct</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">GetVersionRsp</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"k\">crate</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">version</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">u8</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"k\">crate</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">code</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">u8</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">param1</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">u8</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">param2</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">u8</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">reserved</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">u8</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"k\">crate</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">version_number_entry_count</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">u8</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"k\">crate</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">version_number_entries</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Vec</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"kt\">u16</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 476958459,
        "sender_full_name": "Alistair",
        "timestamp": 1728988704
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Using <code>Vec</code> fundamentally means that the data will be in a separate allocation, which is not what the original struct does.</p>",
        "id": 476958520,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1728988741
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>What does bindgen generate for the struct?</p>",
        "id": 476958597,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1728988773
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yep. I more meant just a collection of <code>u16</code>s that I can iterate through is what I'm looking for (ideally)</p>",
        "id": 476958635,
        "sender_full_name": "Alistair",
        "timestamp": 1728988793
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It's a private struct, so bindgen isn't running on it. I'll move some things around and see</p>",
        "id": 476958742,
        "sender_full_name": "Alistair",
        "timestamp": 1728988826
    },
    {
        "content": "<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">version_number_entries</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"kt\">u16</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ptr</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">as_ptr</span><span class=\"p\">();</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">len</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"n\">ptr</span><span class=\"p\">).</span><span class=\"n\">version_number_entry_count</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">};</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">arr_ptr</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">addr_of</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"p\">((</span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"n\">ptr</span><span class=\"p\">).</span><span class=\"n\">version_number_entries</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">};</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">core</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">slice</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">from_raw_parts</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">arr_ptr</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">cast</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"kt\">u16</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">(),</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">len</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 476959105,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1728988979
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You're probably going to do something like this.</p>",
        "id": 476959127,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1728988986
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>bindgen says this</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"cp\">#[repr(C, packed)]</span>\n<span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">struct</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">spdm_get_version_rsp</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">version</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">u8_</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">code</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">u8_</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">param1</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">u8_</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">param2</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">u8_</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">reserved</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">u8_</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">version_number_entry_count</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">u8_</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">version_number_entries</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">__IncompleteArrayField</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">__le16</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 476960975,
        "sender_full_name": "Alistair",
        "timestamp": 1728989728
    },
    {
